# W&B Project Agent (docs.wandb.ai)

When the task involves **Weights & Biases**, **wandb**, **W&B Weave**, **W&B Inference**, **W&B Training**, **artifacts**, **sweeps**, or **experiment tracking**, treat this rule as the project agent for that work.

## Canonical sources (use before coding)

1. **Doc index for agents:** [https://docs.wandb.ai/llms.txt](https://docs.wandb.ai/llms.txt) — full sitemap of topics; use it to pick the exact page.
2. **Human landing:** [https://docs.wandb.ai/](https://docs.wandb.ai/) — product overview.
3. After choosing a path from `llms.txt`, **fetch the specific doc page** (same host/path as in the index) and implement from that content. Do not rely on memory alone for API shapes, env vars, or CLI flags.

## Product map (where to look first)

| Need | Start here |
|------|------------|
| `wandb.init`, `log`, runs, dashboards, artifacts, sweeps | [W&B Models](https://docs.wandb.ai/models) → [Quickstart](https://docs.wandb.ai/models/quickstart) |
| PyTorch loops (this repo) | [PyTorch integration](https://docs.wandb.ai/models/integrations/pytorch) |
| Tracing / eval / LLM observability | [Weave](https://docs.wandb.ai/weave) |
| OpenAI-compatible hosted inference | [W&B Inference](https://docs.wandb.ai/inference) |
| Serverless SFT/RL jobs (API) | [W&B Training](https://docs.wandb.ai/training) + API refs under Training Jobs in `llms.txt` |

## Implementation discipline

- **Config:** Prefer `wandb.init(project=..., config={...})` and structured `wandb.log` keys; align names with what the team already logs in training scripts.
- **Secrets:** Use `WANDB_API_KEY` (or login flow); never commit keys or paste them into code.
- **Scope:** Add only the integration the user asked for (e.g. metrics only vs. artifacts vs. sweep). Match existing patterns in the file you edit.
- **Uncertainty:** If the doc page is unclear, say so and quote or summarize the fetched section rather than guessing parameters.

## Anti-patterns

- Inventing REST paths, SDK methods, or Weave decorators not shown in fetched docs.
- Mixing up **Models** (experiment tracking SDK) with **Inference** (HTTP OpenAI-style API) or **Training** (managed jobs) without checking the right section.
